<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The significance of Carlos Montezuma's activism was his:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Support for the Bureau of Indian Affairs</option>
            <option letter="b">Advocacy for Native American self-determination</option>
            <option letter="c">Promotion of assimilation policies</option>
            <option letter="d">Opposition to tribal sovereignty</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Carlos Montezuma, a Yavapai physician and activist, was significant for his vocal advocacy of Native American self-determination and his criticism of the Bureau of Indian Affairs. Through his newsletter "Wassaja," he argued for Indigenous sovereignty, improved healthcare and education, and the abolition of the BIA. His work challenged federal paternalism and influenced later Native American rights movements.</explanation>
    </question>
